<br>
Last I left off, from a *gigantic* thread on this board, the definition, as I understood it, was:<br>
<br>
A hit will be completely mitigated (minimum damage received) 10% of the time.  The evidence seemed anecdotal, but, I guess, reasonable.<br>
<br>
I would love for someone to come out with info on exactly what CS does.<br>
<br>
